alaDoSSlot.description: Slot on which recent suspect packet was received.

alaDoSPortScanClosePortPenalty.name: alaDoSPortScanClosePortPenalty
alaDoSPortScanClosePortPenalty.description: Penalty points added to the total port scan penalty value when a TCP/UDP packet destinated to a closed port is received.

alaDoSPortScanTcpOpenPortPenalty.name: alaDoSPortScanTcpOpenPortPenalty
alaDoSPortScanTcpOpenPortPenalty.description: Penalty points added to the total port scan penalty value when a TCP SYN/FIN packet destinated to a open TCP port is received. No difference between legal TCP packet and port scan packet.

alaDoSPortScanUdpOpenPortPenalty.name: alaDoSPortScanUdpOpenPortPenalty
alaDoSPortScanUdpOpenPortPenalty.description: Penalty points added to the total port scan penalty value when a UDP packet destinated to a open UDP port is received. No difference between legal UDP packet and port scan packet.

alaDoSPortScanTotalPenalty.name: alaDoSPortScanTotalPenalty
alaDoSPortScanTotalPenalty.description: Total port scan penalty value accumulated at present time

alaDoSPortScanThreshold.name: alaDoSPortScanThreshold
alaDoSPortScanThreshold.description: Threshold port scan penalty value. If the total port scan penalty value exceeds this value, a port scan attack is recorded

alaDoSPortScanDecay.name: alaDoSPortScanDecay
alaDoSPortScanDecay.description: Decay speed for the total port scan penalty value. The penalty value is reduced by a factor of the decay value every minute

alaDoSTrapCntl.name: alaDoSTrapCntl
alaDoSTrapCntl.description: Indicates whether the switch will generate SNMP traps for alaDoSTraps. 'Enabled' results in SNMP traps; 'disabled', no traps are sent.

alaDoSARPRate.name: alaDoSARPRate
alaDoSARPRate.description: Rate of ARP Requests, which if exceeded, an ARP Flood attack is detected.

alaDoSPingRate.name: alaDoSPingRate

alaDoSArpPoisonTable.name: alaDoSArpPoisonTable
alaDoSArpPoisonTable.description: A list of IP addresses for which periodic ARP Requests are to be generated, and from which if an ARP Packet is received, an ARP Poison Attack is detected.

alaDoSArpPoisonIpAddr.name: alaDoSArpPoisonIpAddr

alaDoSArpPoisonDetected.name: alaDoSArpPoisonDetected

alaDoSArpPoisonRowStatus.name: alaDoSArpPoisonRowStatus
alaDoSArpPoisonRowStatus.description: enable/disable ARP Poisoning for this IP

ipNetToMediaSlot.name: ipNetToMediaSlot
ipNetToMediaSlot.description: Slot associated with address translation. An address translation not associated with a slot/port pair will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to zero. An address associated with an Ethernet Management Port (EMP) will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to -1. An address associated with a link agg port will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to the link agg id.

ipNetToMediaPort.name: ipNetToMediaPort
ipNetToMediaPort.description: Port associated with address translation. An address translation not associated with a slot/port pair will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to zero. An address associated with an Ethernet Management Port(EMP) will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to -1. An address associated with a link agg port will have ipNetToMediaSlot equal to zero and ipNetToMediaPort equal to the link agg id.

ipNetToMediaChassisId.name: ipNetToMediaChassisId
ipNetToMediaChassisId.description: Chassis Id associated with address translation.

alaDoSTrap.name: alaDoSTrap
alaDoSTrap.description: The DoS trap indicates that the sending agent has received DoS attack

pktDrop.name: pktDrop
pktDrop.description: The pktDrop trap indicates that the sending agent has dropped certain packets (to blocked IP ports, from spoofed addresses, etc).

pktDropType.name: pktDropType
pktDropType.description: Reason index for why this packet was dropped

pktDropIfIndex.name: pktDropIfIndex
pktDropIfIndex.description: Interface index (if_index) of ingress port of this dropped pkt

pktDropCount.name: pktDropCount
pktDropCount.description: The # of pkt drops (within a configured time interval) of this pktDropType that triggered this particular trap instance

pktDropFrag.name: pktDropFrag
pktDropFrag.description: <= 512 bytes of the dropped pkt (dsmac[12], tag[4], etype[2], payload[..512] (0 if DropCount only)

ipCidrRouteScope.name: ipCidrRouteScope

alaIcmpAllMsgStatus.name: alaIcmpAllMsgStatus

alaIpArpFilterType.name: alaIpArpFilterType

alaIpArpFilterRowStatus.name: alaIpArpFilterRowStatus

alaIpServiceTable.name: alaIpServiceTable
alaIpServiceTable.description: Table to enable/disable IP services on switch

alaIpServicePort.name: alaIpServicePort
alaIpServicePort.description: IP service port. To modify the default port, use corresponding MIB attribute below: - ftp : alaIpFtpPort from alaIpFtpConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - ssh : alaIpSshPort from alaIpSshConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - telnet : alaIpTelnetPort from alaIpTelnetConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - http : alaIND1WebMgtHttpPort from alcatelIND1WebMgtMIBObjects in ALCATEL-IND1-WEBMGT-MIB.mib - ntp : can't be modified - snmp : can't be modified - https : alaIND1WebMgtHttpsPort from alcatelIND1WebMgtMIBObjects in ALCATEL-IND1-WEBMGT-MIB.mib

alaIpServiceStatus.name: alaIpServiceStatus
alaIpServiceStatus.description: When read, returns enabled if service and port are enabled, and returns disabled otherwise. When written, enables/disables service and port (although snmp is never fully shut down; if disabled in some VRF, it will run in the default VRF). Note that that http, https, and ntp here are read-only; use alternatives described below to enable/disable service. If you want to block packet and shut down service, use corresponding MIB attribute below: - ftp : alaIpFtpAdminStatus from alaIpFtpConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - ssh : alaIpSshAdminStatus from alaIpSshConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - telnet : alaIpTelnetAdminStatus from alaIpTelnetConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-IP-MIB.mib - http enable : alaIND1WebMgtAdminStatus from alcatelIND1WebMgtMIBObjects in ALCATEL-IND1-WEBMGT-MIB.mib - http disable : alaIND1WebMgtServerStatus from alcatelIND1WebMgtMIBObjects in ALCATEL-IND1-WEBMGT-MIB.mib - ntp : alaIpNtpVrfName (in this mib), and alaNtpEnable and alaNtpBroadcastEnable from alaNtpConfig in ALCATEL-IND1-NTP-MIB.mib - snmp : [no alternative -- use this MIB object] - https : same as http
